<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFAE6A11FD26929C1D77BE99" pageId="85" pageNumber="843" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFAE6A11FD26929C1B27BEB6" blockId="85.[729,1322,1142,1569]" pageId="85" pageNumber="843">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAE6A11FD26929C1A04BFD4" authorityName="R. A. Philippi" authorityYear="1866" box="[730,1028,1221,1254]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magellanicus">Histiotus magellanicus</taxonomicName>
was described as a species and later considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAE6A11FCF9934A1DB6BE06" baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Landbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[773,950,1299,1332]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="843" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">H. montanus</taxonomicName>
. This classification is still discussed, but morphological evidence suggests that this is a distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFAE6A11FD2693D71D77BE99" blockId="85.[729,1322,1142,1569]" box="[730,887,1422,1451]" pageId="85" pageNumber="843">Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFAE6A11FD2693E81D15BEC8" pageId="85" pageNumber="843" type="distribution">
